    "title": "Canadian Rebates for Solar Installations",
    "slug": "canadian-rebates-solar",
    "content": "<h1 id=><strong id=>Canadian Rebates for Solar Installations</strong></h1><p id=>As energy costs continue to rise, more Canadians are turning to solar power as a smart, sustainable investment. The good news? There are generous federal and provincial rebate programs designed to make switching to solar more affordable than ever.</p><h2 id=><strong id=>Canadian Federal Rebates &amp; Low-Interest Loans</strong></h2><p id=>The <strong id=>Canada Greener Homes Program</strong> offers rebates of up to <strong id=>$5,000</strong> for installing solar photovoltaic (PV) systems. Homeowners can also access <strong id=>low-interest financing of up to $40,000</strong> through the Greener Homes Loan to cover installation costs. These programs aim to help Canadians reduce energy consumption while improving property value and comfort.</p><p id=>To qualify, homeowners must complete an energy audit before and after installation, ensuring their new solar system meets program efficiency standards.</p><h2 id=><strong id=>Provincial Programs</strong></h2><p id=>Depending on where you live, additional rebates and incentives may be available:</p><ul id=><li id=><strong id=>New Brunswick:</strong> The <strong id=>NB Power Total Home Energy Savings Program</strong> offers rebates for eligible solar installations and energy efficiency upgrades.</li><li id=><strong id=>Nova Scotia:</strong> The <strong id=>SolarHomes Program</strong> provides rebates covering up to <strong id=>$3,000–$5,000</strong> toward solar PV systems for homeowners.</li><li id=><strong id=>Prince Edward Island:</strong> Through the <strong id=>Solar Electric Rebate Program</strong>, residents can receive up to <strong id=>$10,000</strong> based on system size and energy output.</li><li id=><strong id=>British Columbia:</strong> The <strong id=>CleanBC Better Homes Program</strong> offers rebates and supports for clean energy retrofits, including solar installations.</li></ul><p id=>These regional programs can often be combined with federal incentives — maximizing total savings for homeowners.</p><h3 id=><strong id=>Why Go Solar Now</strong></h3><p id=>With installation costs dropping and rebate funding still widely available, now is the ideal time to invest in solar energy. Homeowners not only lower monthly electricity costs but also future-proof their homes against rising utility rates and contribute to a cleaner energy grid.</p><h3 id=><strong id=>Partner with Greenfoot Energy</strong></h3><p id=>At <strong id=>Greenfoot Energy Solutions</strong>, we simplify the process — from system design to installation and rebate assistance. Our experienced team ensures your project qualifies for maximum incentives and delivers optimal performance for decades to come.</p><p id=><strong id=>Ready to explore solar for your home?</strong> Contact Greenfoot today to schedule a free consultation and discover how much you can save with current Canadian solar rebates.</p>",
