    "title": "Greenfoot Energy Systems Renews Partnership with Saint John Energy",
    "slug": "greenfoot-partners-with-saint-john-energy-2025-update",
    "content": "<h1 id=><strong id=>Greenfoot Energy Systems Renews Partnership with Saint John Energy</strong></h1><p id=>At Greenfoot Energy Systems, we’re proud to continue our partnership with the innovative team at Saint John Energy — helping homeowners across New Brunswick make their homes more efficient, affordable, and comfortable through smarter energy solutions.</p><h2 id=><strong id=>Delivering Comfort Through Innovation</strong></h2><p id=>We’re the official <strong id=>installation and maintenance partner</strong> for the Saint John Energy <strong id=>Mini-Split Heat Pump Rental Program</strong>, giving customers an affordable way to upgrade to efficient heating and cooling without the upfront cost.</p><p id=>Our Greenfoot technicians handle every step — from installation to ongoing service — so homeowners can enjoy peace of mind knowing their system is backed by local professionals who care about long-term comfort and performance.</p><p id=>This rental option remains one of the few of its kind in Atlantic Canada. Its popularity continues to grow because it’s simple, flexible, and completely maintenance-free for the customer.</p><p id=><strong id=>Learn more about the program:</strong><br><a href=https://www.saintjohnenergy.ca/products-and-services/heat-pump-rentals id=>https://www.saintjohnenergy.ca/products-and-services/heat-pump-rentals</a></p><h2 id=><strong id=>Why This Partnership Matters</strong></h2><p id=>Since first partnering in 2021, our collaboration with Saint John Energy has grown stronger each year. Together, we’ve helped hundreds of New Brunswickers access efficient home heating and cooling through a trusted local program.</p><p id=>The rental model gives homeowners a way to enjoy all the benefits of a heat pump — lower bills, reliable comfort, and reduced carbon footprint — without the upfront expense. And because Greenfoot handles installation and service, every customer receives consistent, high-quality support at no extra cost.</p><h2 id=><strong id=>Joint Commitment to Local Energy Efficiency Solutions in New Brunswick</strong></h2><p id=>Saint John Energy’s <strong id=>Utility of the Future</strong> initiative continues to lead the way in customer-focused energy innovation — and we’re proud to play a key role in that journey.</p><p id=>Both organizations share a belief in local service, practical efficiency solutions, and a commitment to helping Atlantic Canadians make sustainable energy choices.</p><p id=><strong id=>Explore more about Saint John Energy’s initiatives:</strong><br><a href=https://www.sjenergy.ca id=>https://www.sjenergy.ca</a></p><h3 id=><strong id=>Learn More</strong></h3><p id=>Homeowners can learn more about Saint John Energy’s Mini-Split Heat Pump Rental Program by visiting</p><p id=>https://www.saintjohnenergy.ca/products-and-services/heat-pump-rentalsor by calling <strong id=>506-658-5252</strong>.</p><p id=>For more information about Greenfoot Energy’s full range of energy-efficiency services, visit<br><a href=https://www.greenfootenergy.ca?utm_source=chatgpt.com id=>https://www.greenfootenergy.ca</a><br>or call <strong id=>1-844-448-0787</strong></p>",
